betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Wireless Charging Antenna is an upgrade from the Wireless Charger in the way that it has a bigger range.

One of the main things that you are going to need in this pack and especially early on are mob drops. To obtain them you are going to need to make an enclosed room where mobs can spawn or a mob dropper.
You can't craft a regular Furnace yet, so for cooking and smelting you are going to need the next best thing: a Dirt Furnace. It works just like a regular Furnace, but it uses 3 times more fuel.

In order to make many basic items from Sky Resources and a few other mods, you are going to need to construct a multiblock Combustion Chamber.

 You can see how to do that and how to use it in the Sky Resources 2 guide.

You can hold right-click and let go with a Water Extractor to collect Water from Leaves, Snow or Cacti.

 You can place Water by shift+right-clicking and with it make an infinite Water source.
Now that you have Water and Lava, you can make a traditional Cobblestone Generator.
With a Rock Grinder, you can grind certain materials down into other materials.

To start off with the alchemical part of Sky Resources, you are going to need to make an Alchemical Fusion Table. With it, you are going to be able to make many different Alchemical items.

 For it to work however, you are going to need a Catalyst such as Primus Alchemical Dust. Every recipe uses up a certain amount of the Catalyst, represented by the green bar. Every Catalyst has a yield, which determines how much the purple bar gets filled during every recipe, which when full gives you an output.

The Stone Casing gives your Combustion Chamber a higher maximum amount of Heat Units and the Stone Combustion Heater lowers the amount of fuel used per Heat Unit, as well as the Heat Units used per recipe, but prevents you from using the Trapdoor.
Magmafied Stone, when touching Crystal Fluid, drops Cobblestone.
By inserting Water into Dirt, you are able to make Clay or Compressed Clay (by inserting it into Compressed Dirt).
Now that you have a Condenser setup, with Crystal Fluid and Iron Alchemical Dust, you can make an Iron Ingot.
The Enhanced Wireless Charging Antenna has a better range than the regular one and can even have its range expanded in a certain direction with Extensions.
While you can twerk or sprint around your Saplings to grow the faster, you can use Plant Matter on them to grow them instantly.
End Steel is an end-game EIO alloy made with Obsidian, End Stone and Dark Steel. Darl Steel is another alloy ,made with Iron, Coal and Obsidian.
To make Redstone needed for machines and Redstone mechanisms, you are going to need 880 HU, which the Iron Casing allows you to reach.
This unlocks small bits from a few mods that will help you with early-game automation.
To get passive mobs to spawn and to obtain different seeds, you are going to need to make a Grass block.

Now that you can make Blaze Powder, you can craft it into a block and put it above a Torch to obtain Lava. Melting it could take a few minutes, but if you're lucky, it could even take only a few seconds.

This is everything you need in order to construct the smallest possible Extreme Reactor.

 Extreme Reactors use Yellorium for generating large amounts of power.
You can grind Gravel to turn it into Sand.
You can grind Cobblestone to turn it into Gravel.

In order to make Ingots, you are going to need a setup for Condensation. You can see how to make the most basic of setups in the Sky Resources guide on the Metal Creation page. Keep in mind that the bottom block can be any inventory, such as a Chest.
By breaking Grass, you can obtain Seeds for many different useful crops.

Through Life Infusion you can make plants needed for progression, by using health and 2 certain items.

 If you started on the Desert Island, you already have a Sandstone Infusion Stone, but if you didn't, you are going to need to make a Dehydrated Cactus through Combustion and hydrate it with a Water Extractor.

 You can learn more about how it works in the Sky Resources guide.
This unlocks Aether Legacy and Open Blocks.
Another thing that you can make with a combustion chamber with an Iron Casing is Netherrack.
The Enhanced Chassis allows you to enhance your industrial EIO machines.
Worms can be obtained by tilling Grass. They keep create Farmland in a 3x3 area.
Now that you have a Netherbrick Casing, you can make Glowstone with Gunpowder and Blaze Powder.
Wooden Spikes damage mobs until they get to half a heart.
Stone Spikes damage mobs and kill them.

Using a Freezer, you can, well, freeze different materials to turn them into other materials. It's also one of the easiest ways of making Dirt.

 If you started on the Snow Island, you already have this, but if you didn't, you can make Snow through Combustion, shift+right-click on blocks of Snow to duplicate them and craft a Mini Freezer.
While the Mini Freezer works, it's not really that fast. It's best to make a multiblock Iron Freezer to freezer more things faster.
Golden Spikes damage mobs and make them drop experience.
Diamond Spikes damage mobs and make them drop player-only drops, such as Lootbags.

The Crucible Inserter holds up to a stack of Crystal Shards and automatically throws them in the Crucible when it has room for them, making it so that you don't have to go to it and throw 3 shards in it every few minutes anymore.

To start off, you are going to need to collect the 2 Spruce Wood Bark blocks and use them to make a Crafting Table and a Wooden Hoe, with which you can till the Coarse Dirt into Dirt and the Dirt into Farmland. You then need to harvest the Wheat via right-click and twerk near it to regrow it. Once you have a few stacks of Wheat, you can make Thatch (preferably Slabs) and with it you are going to want to make a mob spawner. Then, all you need is Bonemeal with which you can crafting a Spruce Sapling. If you ever get hungry, while you can't make Bread, you can simply eat the Wheat.
The Basic Solar Panel can generate 4RF/t during the day.
The Hybrid Solar Panel can generate 64RF/t during the day.
The Tinker's Hammer for connecting certain Embers blocks.
The Crucible is used for melting Blaze Powder Blocks into Lava and Crystal Shards into Crystal Fluid.
With Life Infusion, you can make Saplings that grow Slime.
Purple Slime is more useful than Blue Slime, so you should also make a Sapling for it.
For making Tinker's tools with Fire Aspect, you are going to need Magma Slime. Luckly you can also make a Sapling for it.
To reach a high amount of Heat Units, you are going to need a Netherbrick Casing. Keep in mind that it has really low efficiency.

Droppers are fine and all, but continuously pressing a Button for getting it to drops items isn't fun. Don't worry though. You can now make a Quick Dropper which doesn't require a Redstone singal (unless you want to turn it off). Keep in mind that it cannot be used with a Wooden or Stone Combustion Heater.
The Sturdy Casing is needed for making most Forestry machines.
The Carpenter uses power, items and a certain fluid to make a certain item.
The Squeezer uses power from Squeezing certain items.
The Pipette is a great tool for moving around fluids early on. The great thing about it is that there's not a minimum amount of fluid it can hold.
The easiest way of storing fluids is in Barrels.

The Combustion Collector automatically collects the Combustion recipe outputs, making it so that you don't have to empty it out after every recipe. Keep in mind that it cannot be used with a Wooden or Stone Combustion Heater.
The Advanced Solar Panel, besides for generating a good bit of RF during the day, can also generate a bit during the night.
Now that you have a Carpenter and a Squeezer, you can make Impregnated Casings, needed for some Forestry and Binnie's Mods machines, and Impregnated Sticks, needed for Impregnated Frames.
To be able to construct all the Multiblock IE machines, you are going to need an Engineer's Hammer.
For making Coke Coal and Creosote Oil, you are going to need a Coke Oven.
For making Steel and starting off with mid-game, you are going to need a multiblock Blast Furnace.
The Projector allows you to see where everything in an IE multiblock goes in the world, helping you build it.

Demon Ingots are obtained by throwing Gold into Lava that's surrounded by Nether Bricks on all sides, besides the top and bottom. Keep in mind that it has a small chance to eat up your Gold without giving you anything.
Light Matter machines are the most efficient Sky Resources machines.
The Ultimate Solar Panel can generate over 1kRF/t during the day.
The Plasma Generator uses Plasma to generate a lot of RF.
The Quantum Solar Panel is the best Solar Panel.
The Crucible allows you to melt Glowstone.
The Grindstone allows you to make Blades.
A Cauldron can be used for cleaning Dirty Gems and possibly getting metals from Crushed Stone and Netherrack.
Similar to Crystallizers from other mods, the NuclearCraft one can be used for turning fluids the corresponding Dusts.
Secundus Alchemical Dust is the second Catalyst and allows you to get twice the output from your Alchemical Fusion Table, most of the time.
The Tier 1 Lightning Rod generates about 350kRF per strike.
You can make a Reinforced Blast Furnace and add Preheaters to it to make it run faster.
Almost every multiblock machine from IE uses at least one type of Engineering Block.
The Tier 2 Lightning Rod generates about 1.75MRF per strike.
The Empowerer uses power and the items on Display Stands 3 blocks away from it on every side to empower certain items.
The Fuel Input Machine allows you to speed up your Smeltery, by putting Speed Upgrades and Solid Fuel in it.
With the Stirling Engine, you can generate RF from the heat of the molten fluids in Seared Tanks.
The Tier 3 Lightning Rod generates about 8.75MRF per strike.
The Fluid Agititor allows you to mix fluids and an item.
The Tier 4 Lightning Rod generates about 43.75MRF per strike.
The Tier 5 Lightning Rod generates about 218.75MRF per strike.
The Tier 6 Lightning Rod generates about 1093.75MRF per strike.
The Compression Chamber can fill up certain items with certain fluids.
The Mob Disassembler allows you to break vanilla mobs down into their basic components.
The Metal Cutting Machine allows you to make Wires, Gears Blunt Drills (that can then be turned into regular Drills with the Grindstone).
The Circuit Scribe allows you to etch patterns on Quartz Plates.
The Propane Furnace uses Propane instead of fuel to function.
The Fluid Extraction Drill simply extracts fluids from the void. In some chunks it will extract Sulphur and in some Propane.
The Chop Saw allows you to get 6 Planks from a Log and to make Quartz Plates.
The Drill Grinder allows you to make Dusts with which you can make alloys.
The AntiBarrel can store a large amount of non-stackable items.
You can travel to the Aether through a portal which is a 5x4 frame of Glowstone activated with a Bucket of Water.
The Magnetizer turns Iron into a Magnet, when given a constantly repeating Redstone signal.
When exploring the Aether, you will find a few Clouds and Quicksoil.
Grout is needed for making Seared Bricks with which you'll be able to make the many multiblocks of Tinker's Construct.
You can cross-breed Carrots and Potatoes on Mycelium to create Spores.
The Digital Miner, when powered, can mine ores in a area. What makes it special is that you can filter what it mines.
The Petal Apothecary is used for creating Generating and Functional Mana Flowers.
The Pure Daisy is used mainly for transmuting Wood into Livingwood and Stone into Livingrock.
The Mana Pool is used for storing Mana and for infusing certain items with it, when they're dropped in it.
The Mana Spreader collects Mana from Mana-generating flowers or adjacent Mana Pools and transfers it to the blocks in the direction it is facing.
The Wand of the Forest is used for configurating Mana-accepting blocks.
The Endoflame generates Mana from fuel.

These are all the Mana infused items.

 The main one that you are going to need for progressing through Botania and the pack is Manasteel.
The Atomic Reconstructor uses RF to shoot a laser which can transmute the blocks and items that it hits.
Tertius Alchemical Dust is the 3rd Alchemical Dust and the last early-game one. It multiplies the output by 4 and 5, switching between them after every recipe.
To be able to make basic Tinker's Construct Tools, you are going to need a few "Tables".
With Wood, you can make some simple Chests.
The easiest way of transferring items is with Wooden Hoppers. However, just like regular Hoppers, they cannot transfer upwards.
In order to make certain alloys, you are going to need to build a Smeltery.
Now that you have Knightslime and Manyullyn, you can make an upgrade that will allow your Smart Output to work as a Casting Basin.
For automating the Smeltery, you are going to need a Smart Output. Be careful though, it's really fast.
The Blood Extractor is used for collecting Blood by simply having it in your inventory when killing a mob or by shift+right-clicking on Blood on the ground, where a mob took fall damage.
By throwing a Dark Gem in a 5-block-pool of Blood, it'll absorb the Blood and turn into a Dark Power Gem.

By placing Blood on the ground, it'll soon harden and you'll be able to use a Flint And Steel on it to turn it into Hardened Blood Shards, or you can you can put it in a Drying Basin or a Casting Basin to harden it and them smelt it.
The Blood Infuser simply infuses items with Blood.
The Blood Chest uses Blood for repairing items.
Now that you have Seared Bricks, you can craft a Tool Forge and with it make advanced TIC tools.
The are many upgrades that you can add to the Smart Output to suit your needs.
The Promise of Tenacity I allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 40 buckets of Blood and unlocks a slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.
Promises of Velocity make your Blood Infuser work faster.
Promises of Productivity decrease the amount of Blood used in recipes in the Blood Infuser.
The Promise of Tenacity II allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 160 buckets of Blood and unlocks a second slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.
The Promise of Tenacity III allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 640 buckets of Blood and unlocks a third slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.
Blood trees' parts can be squeezed to obtain more Blood than the amount that was used to make them. Keep in mind that the Leaves drop Dead Bushes, so it's best to squeeze them.
You can costruct a Broom with customizable parts that allows you to fly for the cost of some Blood.
The Clossal Blood Chest is simply a larger Blood Chest.
The Sanguinary Pedestal automatically collects Blood from the ground. In order for it to collect it from mobs however, you are going to need a Spiked Plate on top of it.
The basic Calculator is used for msking basic Calculator items.
The Atomic Calculator will allow you to make the Fire Diamonds needed for Empowered Restonia Crystals.
The Scientific Calculator will allow you to make Restone Ingots, needed for making Pistons, as well as a few other Calculator items.
Alternating Flux is higher tier of energy than RF. It can be transferred, but it cannot be used in machines. For that you are going to need a Transformer.
With the Scientific Calculator, you can make a Sapling that grows Amethysts.
With the Empowerer you can make Rock Crystal Ore. You can then use the Atomic Reconstructor on a Rock Crystal to make a Floating Crystal.
The Stone Separator can separate Ores and Wood.
Link the Floating Crystal to Iron Ore to turn it into Starmetal Ore.

For making Tech Reborn Cables, you are going to need Rubber.

 To make Rubber, you are going to need to grow a Rubber Trees, collect the Sap that shows up on its Logs from time to time with a Treetap, and smelt it.
You can make portable Generators that charge up Batteries and similar items in your inventory. The most basic one is the Survivalist one.
The Basic Machine Frame is needed for making the simplest of Tech Reborn machines.

The Rolling Machine is used for making certain metal items needed for progression.

 In expert mode, this includes Buckets.
For getting Rubber from every part of a Rubber tree, extracting Fluids from Cell and a fww other things, you are going to need an Extractor.
The Compressor is used for making Plates with power.
The Alloy Smelter is a powered Iron Allow Furnace.
The Rock Cleaner uses Water and Power to automatically clean Dirty Gems and Crushed Stone and Netherrack.
The Rock Crusher uses power to automatically grind materials and has a 3 times higher chance for giving outputs.
With the Aqueous Concentrator you can automatically insert Water and with the Aqueous Deconcentrator you can automatically extract Water.
By piping Ember Shards or Crystals in an Ember Activator, you can turn them into raw Ember energy.
The Induction Smelter allows you to get some extra items from smelting.
For transferring Ember, you are going to need Ember Emitter and Receptors. They need to be connected via the Tinker's Hammer and the Emitters need a redstone signal to work.
The Mixer Centrifuge uses Ember to mix 2 different molten metals and make alloys.
Dawnstone is an alloy of Gold and Copper that can only be made in the Mixer Centrifuge.
The Stamper uses Ember and Stamps to shape molten metals.
The Magma Crucible uses power to melt certain items.
Signalum is an alloy of Copper, Silver and Redstone.
Lumium is an alloy of Glowstone, Tin and Silver.
Enderium is an alloy of Resonant Ender, Platinum and Lead.
Manyullyn is an alloy of Cobalt and Ardite.
The Electric Furnace uses parts instead of fuel to function.
The Tempering Oven allows you to make Tempred Iron Ingots and Tempered parts that last longer. In order to do that, it needs to be given a Redstone signal for a set amount of time.
The Cinder Plinth uses Ember to turn mundane materials into Ash.
The Beam Cannon usses Ember to fire a beam that can either kill a line of mobs or activate an Exchange Tablet.
Before you can get into the alchemical part of Embers, you are going to need Aspecti.

The Exchange Tablet allows you to make more advanced Embers items. The crafting process isn't simple though. In the middle you need to have the Exchange Tablet. On it, you can place items. Near it there need to be Pedestals. Every Pedestal needs to be marked with an Aspectus. Look up the recipe for whatever you want to make, in JEI, put the corresponding items on the tablet, fill up the Pedestals with the corresponding Aspecti with an amount of Ash between the amount shown and fire the Cannon at it. If the amount of Ash was incorrect, you'll get Alchemical Waste that will tell you how much you were off by.

The Stabilization Table turns charged Unprimed Energy Cores into regular Energy Cores. For that it requires Stationary Magnets 2 blocks away from it on all 4 sides, that are given a constantly repeating Redstone signal. If they aren't given a Redstone signal at the same or are given one for way too long, this machine will explode.
The Metallurgic Infuser is used for making all the different Alloys needed for crafting all the different Mekanism machines.
The Latex Fluid Extractor collects Latex from trees, slowly breaking them in the process.
The Latex Processing Unit turns Water and Latex into Tiny Dry Rubber. With that, you can make Plastic.
For obtaining Essence, you can either make a Mob Crusher that kills mobs and collects it from them or a Resourceful Furnace that can smelt 4 items at a time and produces it after they have smelted.
Osgloglas is an alloy of all the Mekanism ingots.
To make HOP Graphite, mainly needed for making Graphite Electrodes used in the Arc Furnace, you are going to need a multiblock Squeezer.
By putting Bog Earth around Water, it'll slowly turn into Peat. Peat can be used as a fuel or it can be smelted into Ash.
The Autocrafting Unit uses Gears to autocraft items. It keeps one of every items and automatically balances stacks.
The easiest way of transferring fluids is with Faucets and Channels. They cannot however transfer upwards.
To be able to melt different materials, you are going to need a Porcelain Melter and Porcelain Tank filled with Lava or a Porcelain Heater filled with fuel below it.
To be able to cast different items, you are going to need a Porcelain Casting Table and a Porcelain Casting Basin.
The Iron Casing is needed for crafting most AA machines.
When mining in the Aether, you will find Zanite and Ambrosium.
The Wood Casing is needed for crafting the simplest AA blocks.
The Biosynthesys Unit spawns to mob that drops the item in it.
You can infuse Electrum and Diamonds with Destabilized Redstone to turn them into their Fluxed version.
The Device Frame is needed for crafting TE devices.
The Chemical Oxydizer can turn certain items into fluids.
TE has its own Energy Cell that can be upgraded in several ways.
The Machine Frame is needed for crafting TE machines.
The Rotary Condensentrator can turn liquids into gases and vise versa.
The Electrolytic Separator allows you to separate fluids into gases.
N The Chemical Infuser can mix gases.
The Chemical Dissolution Chamber can turn Ores into Slurries with Sulfiric Acid.
The Chemical Washer can clean Slurries.
With AA Crystals, you can make several blocks that can interact with blocks in the world.
The Chamical Crystallizer can turn gases into the corresponding Dusts or Crystals.
The Advanced Machine Frame is needed for making the most advanced Tech Reborn machines.
The Chemical Reactor combines 2 different types of items.
To make Tungstensteel, needed for making Dark Matter, you are going to need a multiblock Industrial Blast Furnace with at least 3000 Heat. Keep in mind that you need to fill the multiblock with Lava.
You can turn the Hot Tungstensteel into regular Tungstensteel by putting it in a Vacuum Freezer or in a Fluid Transposer with Cryotheum.
The Recyler turns items into Scrap.
Have you ever wanted to make Clay that can be shaped into any vanilla or TR item? Well now you can!
For making end-game TR materials, you are going to need a multiblock Fusion Reactor.
To turn certain Gem Dusts into Gems and Iridium Alloy Ingot into Plates, you are going to need an Implosion Compressor.

Litherite is needed for making Tier 1 ET machines.

 Left-click with the Assembler on a multiblock Controller to see all the required blocks for the multiblock, right-click to construct it and shift+right-click to pick it up.
The Tier 1 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Erodium.
The Tier 2 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Kyronite.
The Tier 3 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Pladium.
The Tier 4 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Ionite.
The Tier 5 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Aethium.
The Tier 6 Void Ore Miner allows you to collect Prosperity Ore.
Alabaster can be obtained with a Tier 1 Void Resource Miner. This Resource Miner holds 1MRF and uses 6400 per operation.
Mica can be obtained with a Tier 2 Void Resource Miner and is mainly used for crafting Modifiers for the ET multiblock machines. This Resource Miner holds 2MRF and uses 3200 per operation.
The Manufactory can be used as a Crusher and is the most basic NuclearCraft machine.
The Rock Crusher can crush the the various Stone types into some mildly useful materials.
The Mob Disruptor freezes mobs in place.
NuclearCraft has several alloy that can be made in the Alloy Furnace. These 3 are the most-used ones.
The Fluid Infuser infuses items with fluids. It mainly infuses radioactive isotopes with Oxygen.
The Isotope Separator can turn Ingots into the corresponding isotopes.
The Nuclear Furnace uses radioactive materials for smelting instead of fuel.

The Fission Reactor is a multiblock shaped like a box with the sides and corners being left out. It can be filled with different combinations of Cells, moderators and Coolers that will affect the time, efficiency and heat generated by the fuel you put in it.
For your Fission Reactor to work, you are going to need to keep it at a decent temperature. For that, you are going to need Coolers.
The Negative Ion Disperser is basically a Beacon that gives you every effect.
Once your Fission Reactor is properly cooled, you can add Fuel to it. In about a minute, it will become Depleted.
The Fuel Reprocessor will allow you to process the Depleted Fuel Rod.
The Tier 4 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 16 Modifiers and allows you to stack an effect up to level 4.
The Tier 3 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 12 Modifiers and allows you to stack an effect up to level 3.
Ludicrite is the most powerful material in Extreme Reactors.
Dark Matter is the main end-game resource of Sky Resources.
Quartus Alchemical Dust is the best Alchemical Dust in the game.
The Tesla Coil electrocutes nearby mobs.
Find a way to make Wither Skeletons and kill the Wither.
Dark Matter machines have the highest max heat and best speed, but use Dark Matter to function.

Antimony can be used as a replacement for Emeralds in Villager Trades.

 To make it, you need to add an Alchemical Recombulator on the side of the top block of a Mixer Centrifuge and surround it with Pedestals with Aspecti. Fill up the Pedestals with an amount of Ash between that given in JEI and if it's wrong, you'll get Alchemical Waste every few seconds, but the Ash in the Pedestals won't be used up once they have the correct amount.
The Terraneous Extractor extracts Ores from the void.
The Universal Supercharger speeds up adjacent machines.
The Conversion Wand allows you to turn one time of block in an area into another block that you've selected.
You now have everything needed for going to the End and killing the Ender Dragon, but that's not really the end of the pack, is it?
Fluix Crystals are needed for crafting many blocks or items needed for a working ME system.
Instead of making Charged Certus Quartz Crystals through Combustion, you can simply make them with a Charger.
The Tier 2 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 8 Modifiers and allows you to stack an effect up to level 2.
Before you are able to make anything from AE2, you are going to need Presses.
To make many things in AE2, you are going to need Pure Crystals, Just drop the Seeds in Water and they'll slowly grow.
To grow Crystal Seeds faster, you can make a Crystal Growth Chamber and put them in it.
For your ME system to work, you are going to need to turn RF into a different type of power.
Nano Bot Beacons are multiblocks that, when given a set amount of RF, will give you potion effects according to the modifiers they have. The Tier 1 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 4 Modifiers.
The Inscriber allows you to make Processors.
The 1K Storage Cell can store 1024 items.
The 4K Storage Cell can store 4096 items.
The 16K Storage Cell can store 16384 items.
The 64K Storage Cell can store 65536 items.
With a Matter Condenser you can also make Singularities.

The ME Controller is the heart of your ME system. Each one of its sides gives 32 channels, if channels are enabled. They can be arranged in a shapeless multiblock where one must not touch more than 3.
To view what you have stored in your ME system you are going to need a Monitor... or few.
The Conductor Mast uses Lightning to generate power and turn Fire Diamonds into Electric Diamonds.
The Flawless Calculator allows you to make some more complex vanilla and Calculator items.
With the Atomic Calulator, you can make a Sapling that grows Tanzanite.
By combining the Amethyst and Tanzanite Sapling, you can make a.... Pear Sapling....
With the Flawless Calculator, you can make a Diamond Sapling.
The Hunger Processor store hunger points and the Hunger Module slowly regenerates your hunger when it's in your inventory.
The Health Processor store health points and the Health Module slowly regenerates your health when it's in your inventory.
The Algorithm Assimilator automatically harvests Pear and Diamond Saplings.
The Stone Assimilator automatically collects health and hunger from Amethyst and Tanzanite trees.
The Algorith Separato can separate gems.

FactoryTech lets you transfer items with systems of Transport Rollers. You can eject items onto them with the AutoEjector, push items from them into tile entities next to them with a Pulse Piston, insert them into tile entities with Insertion Hatches and carry them upwards with Fan Lifts and Lift Receivers.

 You can transport fluids with Pipes, in the way that you use an Extraction Pump to extract from tile entities into the Pipes.
This unlocks ThaumCraft.
The Apiary allows Bees to breed and create their products.
The Moistener uses Water, Wheat and another item for making certain blocks.
The Bee Attractor uses power and Seed Oil for attracting Bees.
The Centrifuge is mainly used for processing Bee Combs into useful items.
The Bee House is better than the Apiary, but cannot be automated.
The Resonator makes certain items, provided that you have enough GP.
To generate your first GP, you can use a Manual Mill or a Solar Panel.
Now that you have a Resonator, you can make machines that generate GP in other ways.
The Dragon Egg Mill generates a large amount of GP when there's a Dragon Egg on top of it.
You can make Upgrades for your ExU machines and Transfer Nodes. They do however increase the amount of GP needed for them to work.
Reinforced Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Hardened to Reinforced Tier.
Signalum Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Reinforced to Signalum Tier.
Resonant Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Signalum to Resonant Tier.
Hardned Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Basic to Hardened Tier.
Aluminum Brass is an alloy of Aluminum and Copper in a 3-1 ratio. It can be ued for making Casts.
The Teleportation Staff uses power to teleport you whereever you are looking at, no matter the distance.
Enriched Alloy is the simplest alloy made in the Metallurgic Infuser, consisting of only Redstone and Iron.
Reinforced Alloy is Enriched Alloy infused with Diamonds.
The Experience Solidifier turns experience on the ground near it into Solidified Experience.
Atomic Alloy is Reinforced Alloy infused with Obsidian.
The Enrichement Chamber can double the output of gem Ores.
Compressed Redstone, Diamond, Obsidian and Carbon give 80 of the corresponding material in the Metallurgic Infuser.
The Lens of the Miner allows the Atomic Reconstructor to generate Ores when it hits Stone or Netherrack.
The Leaf-Eating Generator uses the Leaves of nearby trees to generate RF.
The Advanced Tier Installer upgrades your Basic Factories to Advanced Factories.
The Ultimate Tier Installer upgrades certain Elite blocks to their Ultimate versions.
The Basic Tier Installer turns your regular Mekanism machines into Basic Factories.
The Elite Tier Installer upgrades your Advanced Factories to Elite Factories.
The Coal Generator uses the types of Coal to generate RF.
Jungle Bees can pruduce Silk.
One of the most common Bee products is Honey.
Different Bee species gives different types of Wax.
You can process Honey Drops into Propolis or obtain it as a product from some Combs.
The Apiarist's set allows you to get close to Bees that would normally hurt you.
The Portable Analyzer gives you more information about whatever you're analyzing, provided that you have Honey Drops in it.
The Infinitato, when right-clicked, gives you every positive vanilla potion effect.
The Ranged Collector collects items that you've filtered, in a 6x6 area.
Silky Jewels can be added to your tools to give them Silk Touch.
Osmiridium is an alloy of Osmium and Iridium.
The Mob Slaughter Factory kills animals to collect certain fluids.
The Enhanced Vat can store 10 times more power and work two times faster than the regular one.
By putting Pink Slime on the ground, it will turn into a Pink Slime.
The Laser Base, when powered by 4 Laser Drills, can collect Ores from the void.
The Enchanter allows you to make certain items from Extra Utilities and to enchant items with power.
Enchanted Ingots can be made with Gold and Lapis in the Enchanter.
You can make Evil Infused Ingots with a Nether Star and Iron in the Enchanter.
Magical Speed Upgrades stack up to 16.
The Ultimate Speed Upgrades stack up to 64.
You can capture a Villager and use it in an Exchanger to automatically trade with it.
MV Wires move around more RF than LV Wires and can still be insulated.
HV Wires move around a large amount of RF, but can't be insulated.
The Lightwell turns certain materials into Liquid Starlight, Water and Lava.
To make a Luminous Crafting Table and a Resonating Wand, link the Floating Crystal to a Crafting Table and use the recipe in the Astral Tome. The Astral Tome is craftable using the same method.
The Dense Storage Cel can hold 16MAE.

Now that you have a Security Terminal, you can add a Wireless Access Point to your ME system, craft a Wireless Crafting Terminal, craft that together with a regular Fluid and Gas Terminal to turn it into a Unviersal Wireless Terminal and put it in the top right slot of the Security Terminal to link it to your ME system.

 You can switch between its modes by shift+right-clicking.
You've completed every quest on Basic Resources.
The multiblock Vacuum Freezer allows you to freeze certain items. That's about all it can do.
The Industrial Centrifuge is used for turning certain items into their basic components, just like every other Centrifuge in this pack.
The Tier 6 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 24 Modifiers and allows you to stack an effect up to level 6.

The Industrial Grinder is a multiblock that can grind down items.

 Note: Water goes in the middle.
For making certain parts and making some craftable parts cheaper, you are going to need an Engineer's Workbench.
The Runic Altar is used for creating Runes.
The Draconic Core is needed for starting off with Draconic Evolution.
The very first thing you are able to do with your Focusing Wand is turning Redstone into Psidust.
Once you reach level 10 of Psi, you are able to turn Gold into Psimetal.
Once you reach level 15 of Psi, you are able to turn Diamonds into Psigems.
The Bottler automatically fills up fluid containers.
In the End, you are able to turn Coal into Ebony and Quartz into Ivory.
To start off with Psi, you are going to need to construct a basic Focusing Wand.

To make different spells you are going to need a Spell Programmer and to cast them you are going to need to put them on a Spell Bullet and then add it to your Focusing Wand. However, you are also probably going to want to construct a better Focusing Wand.
The Fusion Crafting setup consits of a Fusion Crafting Core and Crafting Injectors placed anywhere in a 3x3 from the Core in any direction.
The Tier 5 Nano Bot Beacon can hold 20 Modifiers and allows you to stack an effect up to level 5.
With Fusion Crafting, you can make Wyvern Cores and use them to upgrade the Injectors.
With Dragon Hearts, you can turn Draconium into Awakened Draconium.
With Awakened Draconium, you can once again upgrade your Crafting Injectors.
When cross-breeing crops, the Watering Can is your best friend.
With Awakened Draconium, you can make some of the strongest armor in the game. It has it's own shield. Once it's done, you'll actually start taking damage.
This unlocks EnderIO.
With Awakened Draconium, you can make some really configurable tools.
After going 5k blocks in the End in any direction, you will find a Chaos Dragon.
This unlocks EnderIO.
Now that you have Chaos Shards, you can dupe them and then use them to make Chaotic Cores. With them, you can upgrade your Crafting Injectors to their max tier.
With an Altar, you can make Healing Stones that can be eaten to heal yourself.
The Draconic Chest is the largest Chest in the game. Besides for storing, it can be used for powered smelting.
You can construct a large Energy Core that can store trillions of RF.
The Salt Mixer can mix Salts together.
The Supercooler cools down fluids.
The Neutron Irradiator uses Neutron on fluids to create other materials.
By setting Bedrock on Fire, you have a chance of obtaining Grains of Infinity. They are the main crafting component of EnderIO.
The Chamical Reactor causes 2 fluids to react.
The Machine Chassis is the base crafting component for almost all NuclearCraft machines.
The Uranium RTG generates 4RF/t.
N The Plutonium RTG generates 100RF/t.
The Americium RTG generatoes 50RF/t.
The Californium RTG generates 400 RF/t.
You can add Expanders to your tools to make them mine in a larger area.
By using Moss on a Bookshelf, you can turn it into Mending Moss, which when added to your tools will slowly repair them.
To reinforce your tools or even make them unbreakable, you are going to need Reinforcements.
Drying Racks allow you to dry certain items into Jerkies, Leather and some other things.
With Firewood you can make tools that smelt smeltable blocks that you break with them.
You can add Consecrated Soil to your tools to add Smite to them.
Knightslime is an alloy of Iron, Purple Slime and Seared Stone.
Pigiron is an alloy of Iron, Clay and Blood.
The Transfer Gadget can be blaced on the side of a block for it to auto-output to the block next to it, on the same side.
Alumite is an alloy of Aluminum, Iron and Obsidian.
The Runic Altar allows you to make elemental Runes.
Using elemental Runes, you can make season Runes.
Using season Runes and Mana Diamonds, you can make sin Runes.
Sparks are used for quickly transferring Mana between Mana-accepting blocks.
The Terrestrial Aglomeration Plate is a multiblock that uses half a Mana Pool worth of mana to turn a Mana Diamond, Pearl and Manasteel to make Terrasteel.
The Portal of the Afheim will allow you to transmute Mana infused items into their Elven versions.
These are all the Elven items.
You can obtain a Gaia Spirit by summoning the Gaia Guardian with the structure shown in the Lexica and killing him.
You get a Dice of Fate from killing a Gaia Guardian. You can then roll it to collect a certain relic. Your goal is simple: collect all the relics.
The Pinkinator can be dropped by a Gaia Guardian and allows you to make Withers pink and friendly.
The Botania Brewery allows you to make certain potions using Mana that can be consumed more than once.
With elven items, you can improve your Mana Pool and Spreader.
The Mana Tablet and Band of Mana allow you to carry mana with you.
The River Grate, when placed next to Water and given Wooden Meshes, generates Iron, Nickel and Copper Nuggets. It needs to be between y-level 60 and 70.
When exploring the Aether, you may find a Moa Egg. You can hatch it with an Incubator, using Ambrosium Torches.
The Tier 3 Resource Miner holds 3MRF and uses 1600 per operation.
The Tier 4 Resource Miner holds 4MRF and uses 800 per operation.
The Tier 5 Resource Miner holds 5MRF and uses 400 per operation.
The Tier 6 Resource Miner holds 6MRF and uses 200 per operation.
Mirion is an alloy of all the Botania ingots, Cobalt and Glass.
Hopping Bonsai Pots are one-block automatic tree farms that always keep a Sapling. Simply put the corresponding Soil and Sapling in it and have it generate that tree's products.
The Block Breaker automatically breaks blocks in front of it and outputs them to an inventory behind it.
Vector Plates move mobs and allow them to spawn on them.
With Wither Dust, you can make your Vector Plates faster.
With 8 Fast Vector Plates, you can make the fastest Vector Plates, Extreme Vector plates.
Ectoplasm can be obtained by killing the small Spirits that a occasionally spawn after killing a mob with potions or other magical items.
LV Wires move a small amount of power around and can be insulated.
Gravitite is the most powerful and weirdest ore inthe Aether as it defies gravity.
You can make Gloves that increase your damage and a Cape because why not?

Colossal Chests are hollow 3x3x3 to 10x10x10 Chests. For them to work, the multiblock needs to have a Colossal Chest Core and for inserting in/out of them, the multiblock needs Colossal Chest Interfaces. It has a chest worth of slots per block, including the empty space in it.
The Copper Colossal Chest has a Copper Chest worth of slots per block.
The Iron Colossal Chest has an Iron Chest worth of slots per block.
The Silver Colossal Chest has a Silver Chest worth of slots per block.
The Gold Colossal Chest has a Gold Chest worth of slots per block.
The Diamond Colossal Chest has a Diamond Chest worth of slots per block.
The Obsidian Colossal Chest is an explosion-resistant Diamond Colossal Chest.
With Clouds, you can make a Golden Parachute that you can use to safely float down.
Golden Amber can be obtained by chopping Golden Oak Trees with a Gravitite Axe.
You can find the Valkyrie Queen in a temple-like structures floating in the sky. To be able to battle her, you first need to obtain 10 Victory Medals by killing Valkyries.
While exploring the Aether, you may find a Labyrinth in a cave. At the end of it, is a Lider. You can only attack it with a Pickaxe.
By killing a mob with a Vengeance Ring equipped, its Spirit will stick around for a while. You can then use a Vengeance Focus to lure it to a Box of Eternal Closure and capture it.
You can use a Piercing Vengenace Focus to kill Vengeance Spirits.
The Spirit Reanimator makes the Spawn Egg of that mob that has its Spirit in the Box of Eternal Closure in it.
The Spirit Furnace generates the drops of the mob that has its Spirit in the Box Of Eternal Closure in it, using Blood.
The Uncolossal Chest has only 5 slots, making it useful as a buffer.
The Chicken Catcher allows you to turn Chickens into items.
You can put up to 16 Chickens of the same type and tiers in Roosts to have them generate resources in them.

Similarly to the Magma island, the Bonsai island is not recommended for people that are new to Sky Resources. To start off, you need to harvest the Bonsai Pots, by breaking them to start off with and with an Axe later on. The first thing you are going to want to do is building a mob farm with Wood (preferably Slabs). To not waste time, it's best to go back and forth between building and havesting Bonsai Pots. Once you have some Gunpowder, you are able to set up a Combustion Chamber (which if you don't already know how to set up, you can read about it in the Sky Resources guide). Bones and Rotten Flesh are also quite useful as you can use Bone Meal on Bonsai Pots to help them grow faster and Enriched Bonemeal to grow them instantly. Now all you have to do is craft 4 Plant Matter and make Dirt. As you probably have a lot of Sticks by now, you should probably use them for generating Heat Units in the Combustion Chamber.
These are easiest Rods you can make. Just like all the other Rods from Botania, they use Mana to do a certain thing.
With Psimetal and Psigems, you can make tools and armor with which you can cast spells.
Redstone Arsenal is a mod that adds in Fluxed armor and tools that have special abilities, activated by pressing "V".
The Drawer Controller allows you to interact with multiple Drawers that are next to one another.
The Decotive Diffuser spreads potions in an area.
The Fluid Transposer allows you to fill Tanks and other blocks and items that can store fluids and allows you to make certain items with fluids.
TE has several dusts that can be used for crafting certain items.
The Energetic Infuser allows you to recharge your powered items and make some Fluxed items.
There are several types on Phyto-Grow that can be used to make plants grow faster.
Aqua-Chow can be used in the Aquatic Entangler for collecting Fish.
The Aquatic Entangler uses Aqua-Chow, when it Water to fish out some Fish.
The Phytogenic Insolator uses Fertilizers and power to grow crops faster and more efficiently.
The Thermal Mediator uses coolants to speed up adjacent TE machines.
The Arboreal Extractor collects fluids from trees. Oak and Dark Oak trees give Sap and all other vanilla trees give Resin, with Spruce being the fastest.
TE has several Dynamos for generating RF.
With a Fractinating Still, you can turn Liquified Coal into Refined Oil.
The Centrifugal Separator can separate alloys, Combs and similar items.
The Steel Casing is needed for crafting almost all Mekanism machines.
You can collect Sewage from animals and turn it into Fertilizer.
With a few machines, you can quite efficiently automate a farm.
As the Plant Gatherer harvests trees, it produces Sludge. You can turn this Sludge into some somewhat useful materials.
Essence can be used for processing Ores and Duplicating Mobs.
You can make machines for automatically enchanting, extracting enchantments, applying them and sorting items by them.
The Osmium Compressor is used for making Refined Obsidian and Glowstone Ingots.
The Combiner can turn Stone and resources into the corresponding Ore.

If you want AoE attunement perks to be active without you being there, you can put an Attuned Rock/Celestial Crystal on a Ritual Pedestal, with its multiblock setup, put a Ritual Anchor 3 blocks above it and one where you can the effect to happen, and link them together. You can enchance the effect by connecting a Floating Crystal to the Pedestal and then putting Lenses where green sparkles form.
HDPE can be made with Biofuel, which is made in a Crusher, in a Pressurized Reaction Chamber.
The Robit is a small robot that can follow you, collect dropped items and be used as a Crafting Table, Furnace, Chest and Anvil.
In order to survive on Mars, you are going to need some Thermal Padding, otherwise after a few minutes you'll start freezing to death.
The Simple Alloy Smelter can create EIO alloys using power, but it's horribly inefficient.
The Induction Matrix is a multiblock that can store a large amount of power. It needs to have at least one Induction Cell and Provider surrounded by Induction Casing.

The Boiler is a multiblock that generates Steam.


 These here are the materials needed for the smallest one.

The Turbine is a multiblock that Generates power from Steam.
 
 These are all the materials needed for the smallest possible Turbine.
Mekanism alllows you to turn power or fuel into heat.
The Roost Collector automatically collects the items from roosts in a 9x3x9 area.
One way of transferring around items is with Transfer Pipes.
The Simple SAG Mill works likes other mods' Grinders, but it has additional items it can grind. Yet, it's horribly inefficient.
Pulsating Iron is an alloy of Iron and Ender Pearls.
Unlike other mods' Tanks, EnderIO's can automatically input from and output to adjacent machines. This allows you to use it as a buffer without having Pipes.
The regular SAG Mill can have Grinding Balls added to it to increase the chances of the grinding output.
The Octadic Capacitor allows machines to have a capacity of 500kRF.

The Enhancement Crystal allows you to further enhance your Infinity gear. It will add Looting 10 to the Sword of the Cosmos, give you Night Vision when applied to your Infinity Helmet and give you access to No Clip Mode when applied to your full armor set.
You can make one-block Farms that use Fertilizer, water and RF to grow certain crops faster.
The Circuit Fabricator allows you to make Wafers.
This Compressor can make compressed versions of metals, which somehow don't count as Plates.
The NASA Workbench allows you to make Rockets and other space-related vehihles, provided that you have the corresponding Schematic.
The Double-Layer Capacitor allows machines to have a Capacity of 300kRF.
The Flux Capacitor allows you to carry RF, the Satchel, items, and the Reservoir, fluids.
The Hardened Capacitor and Reservoir have 4 times the capacity the Basic ones do and the Satchel has one more row than the Basic one.
The Reinforced Capacitor and Reservoir have 9 times the capacity the Basic ones do and the Satchel has one more row than the Hardened one.
The Signalum Capacitor and Reservoir have 16 times the capacity the Basic ones do and the Satchel has one more row than the Reinforced one.
The Resonant Capacitor and Reservoir have 25 times the capacity the Basic ones do and the Satchel has one more row than the Signalum one.
The magnetic Centrifuge allows you to separate Gravel into Iron and Nickel Nuggets.

You can construct a Draconic Reactor. It uses Awakened Draconium Blocks to work. As long as it's stabilized, it will generate a large amount of RF and it'll slowly generate Chaos Shards. If the stabilization fails, it will create a large explosion.
To can link a Dislocator to a block and then make a horizontal portal that will take you to it.
You can add upgrades to your Awakened Draconium armor and tools.
The Celestial Manipulator allows you to change the time and weather.
You can make Energy Relay Crystals that can wirelessly transfer a large amount of RF.

The Fusion Reactor consists of a Nuclear Core to which at least one Fusion Connector is connected on every side, surrounded by a square-shaped ring of Electromagnets. For it to work, all Electromagnets need to be powered.
The Purifier uses Blood to transfer the enchantments of your tools onto a Blook.
Entangled Chalices hold the same fluid.
This unlocks AgriCraft and JustAnotherSnad.
The Docking Station allows you to automate Calculators.
The Active Fluid Coller, when given a coolant can cool down a Fission or Fusion Reactor.
You can make machines that collect Nitrogen and Hydrogen from the atmosphere.
The Tier 1 EMC Cell lets you store 1M EMC in your ME system.
You can dye Eggs and throw them for a chance of obtaining dye Chickens.
The Chicken Breeder uses 2 Seeds to breed up to 32 Chickens (16 in both slots).
Give a vanilla Chicken a Book to turn it into a Smart Chicken.
With a Chemical Reactor, you are able to make the most basic resource Chickens.
By breeding the basic and dye Chickens, you can obtain a few new Chickens.
With tier 2 Chickens, you can make tier 3 Chickens.
With tier 3 Chickens, you can make tier 4 Chickens.
The Enhanced SAG Mill can store 10 times more power and work two times faster than the regular one.
4 Miniaturization Field Projectors can create a field that allows you to make certain items from the blocks placed in the field, when a certain item is thrown in it.
The Tiny Compact Machine leads to a 3x3x3 room.
The Small Compact Machine leads to a 5x5x5 room.
The Normal Compact Machine leads to a 7x7x7 room.
The Large Compact Machine leads to a 9x9x9 room.
The Giant Compact Machine leads to an 11x11x11 room.
The Max Compact Machine leads to a 13x13x13 room.
Tunnels allow you to connect your Compact Machines with the outside world.
The Spectre Key gives you your own room in the Spectre Dimension.
With tier 4 Chickens, you can make tier 5 Chickens.
The Timer gives off a Redstone pulse every set amount of ticks.

By using Ectoplasm on a Sapling, it will turn into a Spectre Sapling. It can't be grown via any type of Bone Meal. Its Leaves have a really low chance of dropping Ectoplasm, but if you're lucky, you can get 2 Ectoplasm from one tree.
The Machine Frame is used for crafting the RFTools machines.

You can teleport to a Matter Reciever by selecting it in a Dialing Device near a Matter Transmitter and using it or by linking an Advanced Changed Porter to it. Make sure that they are powered before using them.

The Dimension Inscriber will let you add Dimlets to an Empty Dimension Tab, if you have any, and then turn it into a Realized Dimension Tab. Putting that in a Dimension Builder will create a dimension.
Using the Dimlet Worktable, you can deconstruct and create new Dimlets.
Dimensional Shards are an important resource of RFTools.
The Machine Infuser infuses RFTools machines with Dimensional Shards, making them better in a certain way.
The Machine Base is used for crafting the RFTools devices.
RFTools has many devices that can interact with Redstone in different ways.
The Endergenic Generator is one of the most complicated generators to set up. It uses thrown Ender Pearls to generate RF.
You can make Crafters that can craft multiple items at a time at a really fast pace, but use power.
The Destination Analyzer checks if the destination has power and the Matter Booster lets you teleport to a destination that doesn't have power.
The Builder can interact with a large area of blocks, but what it does depends on how it's configured.
You can save a building on a Shape Card by putting Space Chamber Corner Blocks on its corners and then you can copy it with the Builder.
You can have the Builder mine in an area.
XNet adds cables which can transfer items, fluids and power at the same time, that aren't tile entities, therefore don't lag servers.
The Router allows you to connect channels between multiple networks.
This unlocks AgriCraft and JustAnotherSnad.

The Containment Chalice can be filled up with Liquid Starlight and it will be used instead of the blocks in the Starlight Infuser's structure. If there are 2 next to one another with fluids that can react with each other (for example Water and Lava), they will generate the block that'd be created when they are touching, as a dropped item.
RFTools has a multiblock Elevator and a Booster to speed you up.
The Environmental Controller is essentially a powered Beacon.
The Shield Projector, with Shield Templates, can create a shielded area.
The Block Protector makes blocks blast-resistant.
You can have the Builder pump fluids in an area.
Prosperity Shards are needed for making all the Seeds in Mystical Agriculature.
You can use Inferium to make a more efficient Furnace and Coal.
Tier 1 Inferium Seeds drop 1 Inferium Essence when harvested.
These are all the Tier 1 Mystical Seeds.
The Infusion Crystal allows you to combine 4 of one type of Essence to make another.
With 4 Prudentium Essence, you can make Intermedium Essence.
With 4 Intermedium Essence, you can make Superium Essence.
With 4 Superium Essence, you can make Supremium Essence.
With 4 Supremium Essence, you can make Insanium Essence.
You can make a pet Luggage that follows you and collects items on the ground.
The Prudentium Furnace is 35 percent more efficient than a regular Furnace.
The Intermedium Furnace is 60 percent more efficient than a regular Furnace.
The Superium Furnace is 85 percent more efficient than a regular Furnace.
The Supremium Furnace is 100 percent more efficient than a regular Furnace.
The Ultimate Furnace's efficiency is over 9000 percent greater than that of a normal Furnace..
For most EnderIO machines to work, they are going to need a Capacitor. The Basic one allows machines to have a capacity of 100kRF.
Tier 2 Inferium Seeds drop 2 Inferium Essence when harvested.
The Soulium Dagger is used for a chance of obtaining Mob Chunks from mobs.
The Seed Reprocessor turns resource seeds into their corresponding Essence.
Tier 3 Inferium Seeds drop 3 Inferium Essence when harvested.
Tier 4 Inferium Seeds drop 4 Inferium Essence when harvested.
Tier 5 Inferium Seeds drop 5 Inferium Essence when harvested.
Tier 6 Inferium Seeds drop 6 Inferium Essence when harvested.
These are all the Tier 2 Mystical Seeds.
These are all the Tier 3 Mystical Seeds.
These are all the Tier 4 Mystical Seeds.
These are all the Tier 5 Mystical Seeds.
These are all the Tier 6 Mystical Seeds.
Sometimes when harvesting Mystical Crops, you'll obtain Fertilizer Essence. With 4 of them, you can make Mystical Fertilizer.
For Tier 6 Mystical Seeds to grow normally, they need to have Cruxes below the Dirt they are placed on.
Endergetic Alloy is an alloy of Gold, Redstone and Glowstone.
Capacitor Banks can store RF, but can also be multiblocked. The Basic one can store 1MRF.
Conductive Iron is an alloy of Iron and Redstone.
The Vat can mix a fluid with 2 items.

You can't go into space yet. You don't know where to go yet. So that you don't get lost in space, you should send out a Satelite or few first. To build a Satelite, you are gong to need a Satalite Builder.
With tier 7 Chickens, you can make tier 8 Chickens.
With tier 6 Chickens, you can make tier 7 Chickens.
With tier 5 Chickens, you can make tier 6 Chickens.
With tier 8 Chickens, you can make tier 9 Chickens.
By exploding TNT near a few Iron Ingots, about 80 percent of them will be turned into Compressed Iron Ingots and the rest will be destroyed.
The Air Compressor uses fuel to generate pressure.
The Charging Station allows you to charge certain PC:R items with Pressure.
The Thermopneumatic Processing Plant uses pressure and heat to turn the products of Oil into Liquid Plastic.
The Pressure Chamber is a multiblock that needs to be at least a 3x3x3. It uses a certain amount of pressure to combine or pressurize the items in it.
Pressure Chsamber Interfaces can be used for automatically inputting or exporting from the Pressure Chamber. Place one from the inside to be an output and one from the outside to be an input.
The Plastic Mixer can be used for turning Liquid Plastic into any color of Plastic.
Etching Acid etches Empty PCBs (turns them into Unassembled PCBs).
The Amadron Tablet allows you to trade in Emerads for certain PC:R items and vise versa. It also has random Villager trades that change from time to time.
The UV Lightbox increases the chance for the Empty PCB in it to be successfully extched.
You can finally make a Printed Circuit Board.
For making certain PC:R items, you are going to need a few assembly lines.
The Liquid Compressor is basically an Air Compressor that uses fluid instead of fuel.
All you need to do for this Throphy is to find a Questing Ram and give it Wool of every color.
Flux is obtained by throwing Redstone into Lava.
Flux Networks allows you to make your own wireless RF network that you can insert or extract power from.
The Precision Chamber creates Dirty Circuits from Dirt and Damaged Circuits from Stone.
The Restoration and Reassembly Chamber allow you to repair Dirty and Damaged Circuits.
Electrical Steel is an alloy of Iron, Coal and Silicon.

Welcome to Modern Skyblock 3!

 To start off, you are going to need to create an island and complete stage 1 of it (obtain Dirt and a Sapling). You can press "G" to find out how to do that. Besides for the 6 starting islands listed there, there are 2 more custom islands for which there are pages in the questbook.

 If you're for some reason playing in a default world, just collect Dirt and a Sapling.
The Painting Machine can give blocks or machines other blocks' textures.
The Industrial Machine Chassis is needed for crafting most EIO machines.
This unlocks Tinker's Complement, Ceramics, Tinker's Skyblock and a bit of Tinker's Construct.
The Dawnstone Anvil, in combination with the Automatic Hammer, can automatically deconstruct or repair your tools with different materials.
The Analysing Chamber analyses Circuits and has a chance to give you certain items in the process.
The Ignem Reactor consists of multiple Embers machines running together. It allows you to produce more ember from your Ember Shards.

By throwing Stardust and a Rock Crystal into Liquid Starlight, a Cluster will be created. This Cluster will slowly grow, but can be sped up by placing Starmetal Ore below it. Once it's fully grown, you can break it to obtain a Celestial Crystal.
The Starlight Crafting Altar is a multiblock that has 4 more slots than the Luminous Table.
The Celestial Altar has 8 more slots than the Starlight Crafting Altar.
The Starlight Infuser multiblock allows you to transmute certain items with a chance of using up a block of Liquid Starlight.
Regular Gems are all the Gems obtained from Stone.
Dark Gems are all the Gems obtained from Netherrack.
Light Gems are all the Gems obtained from End Stone.
To start off with Silent's Gems, you are going to need Chaos Essence.
With the Material Grader you have a chance to increase a material's stats.
Passive Chaos Pylons passivly generate Chaos over time, while Burner Chaos Pylons use fuel to generate Chaos.
The Chaos Altar collects Chaos and uses it for either charging Chaos items or transmuting items.
The Chaos Orb stores Chaos and automatically charges your Chaos items.
Glow Roses are simply Roses that glow. Why not have them all?
You can craft a Chaos Node Mover to move Chaos Nodes (those glowing white orbs scattered around the world).
Solar Cells are use in making the Solar Array. The Litherite ones have an efficiecy of 48.
Erodium Solar Cells have an efficiency of 64.
Kyronite Solar Cells have an efficiency of 96.
Pladium Solar Cells have an efficiency of 128.
Ionite Solar Cells have an efficiency of 192.
Aethium Solar Cells have an efficiency of 256.
The Tier 1 Solar Array holds 9 Solar Cells.
The Tier 2 Solar Array holds 25 Solar Cells.
The Tier 3 Solar Array holds 49 Solar Cells.
The Tier 4 Solar Array holds 81 Solar Cells.
The Tier 5 Solar Array holds 121 Solar Cells.
The Tier 6 Solar Array holds 169 Solar Cells.
The Tier 1 Lunar Array generates 1152RF/t.
The Tier 2 Lunar Array generates 2304RF/t.
The Tier 3 Lunar Array generates 4608RF/t.
The Tier 4 Lunar Array generates 9216RF/t.
The Tier 5 Lunar Array generates 18432RF/t.
The Tier 6 Lunar Array generates 36864RF/t.
Magical Wood is a material from Extra Utilities that can be used for making some useful tools and can replace Boookshelves near an Enchantment Table.
The Mecanical User can automatically use items.
You can now make machines that can autocraft, that only take up 1 block and don't use anything to work.
Extra Utilities has many Generators that you can make.
The Rainbow Generator generates large amounts of power when all the other generators are running at the same time.
The regular Capacitor Bank can store 3MRF.
With an Antenna and a few other machines, you can change the biome you are in.
For this you are going to need to make a Villager farm, find one that will accept the Contract, put him in a Golden Lasso and use it to craft a Chunk Loading Ward which loads a 3x3 area of chunks
The Chicken Wing Ring allows you to glide for a while.
The Ring of the Flying Squid allows you to propel yourself upwards for a limited amount of time.
The Angel Ring allows you to fly as long as you have 32 GP.
With an assembly line, you can now make Advanced Pressure Tubes and Compressors that can sustain more pressure.
You are now able to make a machine that turns pressure into RF and one that does the opposite.
The Enhanced Alloy Smelter can store 10 times more power and work two times faster than the regular one.
The Enhanced Combustion Generator can store 10 times more power than the regular one and is 2 times more efficient.
The Fermenter uses power, items and a fluid to create a different fluid.
The Still uses power to turn one fluid into another fluid.
The Canola Press uses power to turn Canola into Canola Oil. Canola Oil can then be used for power in an Oil Generator.
You can use Laser Relays for transferring power, items and fluids wirelessly.
The Ender Casing is used for making the more advanced AA machines and items.
You are able to upgrade your Oven to use power and to upgrade your Fridge to produce Ice and not to keep the last item in a slot from being used.
You can connect Phantom Faces to blocks, so that you'll able to interact with them from a distance.
The Material StoneWork Factory can generate Cobblestone and process it up to 4 times.
By putting Canola Seeds in a Composter they'll turn into Biomass, which you can then smelt to turn it into Bio Coal.

The ME Security Terminal allows you to control who can access your ME system. You automatically gain access by placing it, but you can give permission to others by putting their Biometric Cards in it.
For automating with your ME system, you are first going to need Crafting Storage. Then you can add Patterns to ME Interfaces to tell them what to input and export.
With a Spacial IO you can store an area outlined with Spacial Pylons into a Spatial Cell.
For storing Cells in your ME system you are going to need either a ME Chest or Drive, with the latter being the better one.
The ME IO Port allows you to transfer data between Storage Cells.
With a Matter Condenser you can compress different items or/and fluids into a Matter Ball. You can then use Matter Balls for painting your network.
Portable Cells can be used in a network and by themselves in your inventory.
The Advanced Inscriber acts like a regular Inscriber, but it can hold stacks of items, you can lock items to its slots and it can have 2 more Upgrades. This makes it better for automation.
You can use your ME system to continously export or inport items, fluids or gases from machines.

The EMC Assembler lets you auto-craft items with the EMC stored in your EMC system. Before being able to use it, you are going to need to right-click an Alchemical Tome and put it in only one EMC Assembler in your EMC system, so your EMC system has access to your current knowledge.
The Advanced EMC Assembler can craft faster than the Basic one, as well as 2 things at a time.
The Improved EMC Assembler can craft faster than the Advanced one, as well as 4 things at a time.
The Farmer uses power to harvest and plant crops in an area in front of it.
The Energizer fills items with power and the Enervator empties them.
Bu putting Canola Oil in a Fermentiong Barrel, it'll turn into Refined Canola Oil.
The Tier 2 EMC Cell lets you store 4M EMC in your ME system.
The Tier 3 EMC Cell lets you store 16M EMC in your ME system.
The Tier 4 EMC Cell lets you store 64M EMC in your ME system.
The Basic EMC Condenser lets you turn items that have EMC value of up to 8k EMC, which are piped into it, into pure EMC stored in your ME system.
The Advanced EMC Condenser can turn items that have up to 80k EMC, which are piped into it, into pure EMC and with a peice of Redstone Dust, you can set how Redstone signals affect it.
By throwing a Crystallized Canola Seed into Refined Canola Oil, it'll turn into Crystallized Oil.
By throwing an Empowered Seed into Crystallized Oil, it'll turn into Empowered Oil.
The Drill is essentially a powered Pickaxe.
You can make a Dirt Chest to store your stack of Dirt.
The Copper Chest have 2 more rows than a regular Chest.
The Iron Chest has 1 more row than the Copper Chest.
The Silver Chest has 2 more rows than the Iron Chest.
The Gold Chest has 1 more row than a Silver Chest.
The Diamond Chest has 3 more columns than the Gold Chest.
The Crystal Chest has the space of a Diamond Chest, but you can see what's in it.
The Obsidian Chest is a Diamond Chest, but it's resistant to explosions.
The EnderLink Bag is a portable EnderLink Chest.

EnderLink Chests share an inventory with other EnderLink Chests that have the same color code. You can increase their capacity by 3 slots using Ender Pearls and you can make them private with Diamonds.
Ender Tanks share fluids with other Ende Tanks that have the same color code. You can increase their capacity by 80 buckets using Ender Pearls and you can make them private with Diamonds.
You've completed every quest on Basic Tinkering!
The Junkbox is a Slab in which you can store items.
The Stone Queue outputs items in the order they've been inputted.
Stone Storages are basically Stone Chests that can be stacked on top of each other to increase inventory space. They can only be opened from the front.
The Improved EMC Condenser can turn items that have up to 800k EMC into pure EMC. It can be configured to auto-input from adjacent inventories.
The Ultimate EMC Condenser can turn any item into pure EMC.
The Impulsion Wand is essentially a Grappling Hook.
The Illumination Wand allows you to place down sources of light and to illuminate blocks.
With a Telescope you can find stars in the sky and draw out the constellations on the Papers.
The Attunement Altars allows you to attune yourself or Rock/Celestial Crystals with certain constellations.
The Extreme Crafting Table has a 9x9 grid. It's needed for crafting almost everything in Avaritia.
The Neutron Collector slowly collects Piles of Neutrons.
The Thermionic Fabricator uses Molten Glass and items for making Electron Tubes and other Glass items.
You are able to make a large multiblock Farm that uses Water, RF and Fertlizer to function, but it's one of the most efficient out there.
Using a Soldering Iron, you can add Electron Tubes to Circuits, which you can then add to your Forestry machines to upgrade them.
The Grafter has a 100 percent chance of giving you Saplings from Leaves.
By having Bees near trees or with a Mutatron, you can breed trees. Keep in mind that the trees need to first be analyzed.
After a bit of Bee breeding, you'll get to hellish Bees that produce Phosphor.

You can put crops on Crop Sticks and then put 2 Crop Sticks on top of each other between them in order to breed them. Plants on Crop Sticks can't be grown with Plant Matter or Enriched Bonemeal, but twerking still works.
The Ultimate EMC assembler is the fastest and can craft 8 things at a time.
The Alveary is a much better multiblock version of the Apiary that you can add different parts to in order to acommodate the many different species of Bees.
After breeding crops, you are probably going to want to know how the Seeds have improved. For that you can use a Seed Analyzer. A Journal would allow you to document all mutations.
The Tier 5 EMC Cell lets you store 256M EMC in your ME system.
The Tier 6 EMC Cell lets you store 1.024B EMC in your ME system.
The Industrial Apiary is an upgradable powered Apiary.

The Mutagen Producer creates Mutagen from Redstone, Glowstone, Uranium and Yellorium and can be used in the Mutatron and Advanced Mutatron for breeding bees without any special requires, but yet with a small chance of killing the Bees.
You can collect random genes from Bees, copy them, add them to other Bees or add them to a Template.
With a full Genetic Template, Protein and Liquid DNA, you can create a Bee.
The Essence of Flase Life will allow you to create many useful items, including Dragon Eggs.
You can make a Jar in which you can display Drones.
One of the alloys IE adds is Constantan. You can easily make it in an Alloy Kiln.
Water Wheels generate a set amount of power determined by how much Water is flowing over them and Windmills generate a set amount of power determined by the weather and how high they are.
You can add Windmill Sails to your Windmills to make them generate more power.
For putting your Wire Relays on higher places, you can use Posts and Wallmounts.
The Garden Cloche uses power and Water to grow crops faster.
You can make Wires that can transfer a Redstone signal.
The Tier 7 EMC Cell lets you store 4.096B EMC in your ME system.
The Tier 8 EMC Cell is lets you store 16.384B EMC in your ME system.

The Molten Salt Fission Reactor, unlike the regular one, uses Vessels filled with molten salt fuels and Heaters filled with molten salt coolants. Both of them can be configured for inputting and outputting. Unlike in the regular Fission Reactor, in this one you can put Pipes and whatever else you need for transferring the fluids in and out of the reactor.
By combining Ethanol, made in a Fermenter and Plant Oil, made in a Squeezer, in a Refinery, you can make Biodiesel.
Core Sample Drills give you information about the resources in your chunk.
By putting a Pumpjack in a chunk that has Oil, it'll start slowly collecting it.
By putting Oil in a Distillation Tower, it'll turn into Diesel and you'll get Bitumen as a byproduct.
Lubrican is used for speeding up certain IE multiblocks.
You can make an Advanced Coke Oven and add Preheaters to it to make it run faster.
The multiblock Distillery distills Water and makes Salt in the process.
The Neutron Compressor can turn a large amount of blocks into the corresponding Singularity.
The Ultimate Stew is a combination of many fruits and vegetables. When eaten, it completely fills up your hunger and saturation.
Cosmic Meatballs are a combination of all types of meat. When eaten, they completely fill up your hunger and saturation.

Gardens, when broken, give you different plants.

 Note: The Leaves that you grind must be from a tree i.e. they mustn't be broken and placed.
The Market allows you to trade in Emeralds for crops and other HarvestCraft items.
The Apiary allows you to collect Honey and Wax Combs from Queen Bees.
You can make Traps, place them in the right environment and use the corresponding type of bait to collect passive mob drops.
The Grinder and Presser allow you to process crops and meat without using any power.
Instead of making a passive mob farm, you could grow Soybeans, turn them into Tofu and use that instead of meat in most recipes.

You earn a heart for every 50 different foods you eat, so you are going to want to make as many different foods as possible. To achieve that however, you are going to need some basic cooking utensils.
These are the most basic food ingredients. No matter which food you are making, you are probably going to use one of these.
This unlocks ThaumCraft.
Epic Bacon gives a lot of saturation.
Apple Sauce has a greater nutrition value than regular Apples.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Power Of Stars - Impulsion Wand
betterquesting:10.desc:8: No Description
In order to progress through ThaumCraft, you are going to need a few plants.
This is one of the biggest meals.
This is one of the biggest meals.
In order to start off with ThaumCraft, you are going to need the 6 basic elemental Crystals.
The Cooking For Blockheads book shows you the recipes for every food.
With Cooking For Blockheads II, you can make a cooking table. It will allow you to automatically craft food by selecting it, using the items in the multiblock.
The Kitchen Counter and Fridge are parts of the multiblock where you can store cooking ingredients.
The Cow in a Jar slowly produces Milk and the Sink is an infinite Water source.
The Oven and Toaster automatically cook the corresponding food when needed for a recipe. Additionally, the Oven can store cooking Utensils.
You can put cooking utensils on Tool Racks and ingredients on Spice Racks.
The Iridescent Altar has 4 more slots than the Celestial Altar, but during the crafting process, you are going to need to place items in Spectral Relays around it.
With the Iridescent Altar you can make Constellation Papers, if you haven't already obtained them all from Loot Bags.
With Liquid Starlight and Lava you could make a Sand generator, which drops Aquamarine Shale from time to time.

To enter The Twilight Forest, you are going to need to make a 2x2 body of Water, surround it with Grass, put flowers on the Grass, throw a Dragonstone in the Water and jump in!

 The Twilight Forest is a dimension filled with dungeons and bosses, so obviously the first thing you need to do there is crafting a Dungeon Map.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Naga Courtyard and kill the Naga.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Lich Tower and kill the Twilight Lich.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Labyrinth and kill the Minoshroom.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Goblin Knight Stronghold and kill the Knight Phantom.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Hydra Lair and kill the Hydra.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Dark Tower and kill the Ur-Ghast.

To launch Satelites into space, you are going to need a Satelite Rocket. You are also going to need a 3x3 Launch Pad to place it on and a Fuel Loader to fill it up with Fuel. Once you've got all that, simply fly your Satelite Rocket. At a certain height, you will automatically leave the Rocket and start falling, so hopefully you already have something to prevent you from dying.
Find a Yeti Lair and kill an Alpha Yeti it to obtain its Fur.
To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find an Ice Tower and kill the Snow Queen.
Find a Giant Cloud and kill the miner to obtain his Pickaxe, with which you'll be able to mine Giant Obsidian in a Troll Cave and obtain the Lamp of Cinders.
The Endest Pearl creates a shoft-lasting black hole where it's thrown.
Ironwood can simply be made from Raw Ironwood Materials.
Steeleafs can be found in dungeon Chests in the Twilight Forest.
Fiery Ingots are an alloy of Iron and Firey Blood. Fiery Blood can be found when exploring the Dark Tower.
Knightmetal can be made from an Armor Shard Cluster. Armor Shards can be found in the Goblin Knight Stronghold.
When killing Skeletons with the Skullfire Sword, they drop Wither Skeleton Skulls.
The Seared Furnace is a large multiblock Furnace powered by Lava.
The Tinker Tank is a large multiblock Tank that can store multiple fluids at a time without them mixing.

The Thermal Evaporator is a multiblock which can contiuously turn Water into Brine, making it great for automation. It needs to have a 4x4 base and then a ring at least 2 tall. In the corners of the last layer, you place Advanced Solar Generators.

Ember's Pipes require an Extractor powered with redstone (prefferably with a Lever) for extracting, but are much faster than Factory Tech's Conveyors. They can be filtered with the Item Transfer and there is also an Item Vacuum for sucking up items and an Item Dropper for dropping them.
The Purification Chamber uses Oxygen to turn Ores into Clumps.
The Chemical Injection Chamber turns Ores and Crystals into Shards.
The Vibrank Capacitor Bank can store 5MRF.
Soularium is an alloy of Gold and Soul Sand.

The Turbine Generator is a multiblock that doesn't have a determined shape, but has a minimum and maximum amount of components.

 It uses certain fluids to generate power.
Syngas is made by mixing Water and Coal in the Syngas Producer and is used for generating power in the Steam Generator.
The Steam Turbine Generator uses Steam or Syngas to generate power.
This unlocks Redstone Arsenal, Simply Jetpacks and upgradable things from Thermal Expansion.

You can add a Coolant Port to your Extreme Reactor to cool it with Water, but you could also add another one and right-click it with an Extreme Wrench to output Steam from your Reactor, use it in a Turbine and then pipe it back in as Water.
The Heat Exchanger uses Lava to heat up Water and generate Steam, but also slowly generates Obsidian.
The Worktable allows you to switch between conflicting recipes and can remember up to 9 recipes at a time.

You are going to need a Satelite Controller to collect data from your Satelities. Once it's finished collecting data, you'll get a Research Paper which you can use in a Telescope to discover a planet. To charge up the Telescope, you're going to need to use a Battery from GC or EP.

Killing Chaos Dragons that get harder and harder the farther you go for obtaining Chaos Shards isn't fun. Luckly, you can now craft an Atomic Multiplier. 

 The Atomic Multiplier allows you to quadruple stackable items at the cost of 1.5GRF and 7 Circuits. Keep in mind that creative items, Legendary rewards and items from Extended Crafting and Modular Machinery are blacklisted.
Once you've discovered the Moon, all you need is a Tier 1 Rocket and you are ready to go into space.

Before going to space, you are going to need the correct gear. That includes an Oxygen Mask, Gear, Tank and the actual Space Suit. To fill up your Tank, you are going to need an Oxygen Compressor. To collect Oxygen for it, you can use an Oxygen Collector. If you're not on Earth, the Oxygen Collector will collect Oxygen from Leaves and crops.
With you Tier 1 Rocket, you can travel to the Moon. There you can find Cheese Ore and Meteors with Meteoric Iron.

While exploring the Moon, you may stumble across a dungeon. By defeating the boss in it, you will obtain a Dungeon Key with which you can obtain a Dungeon Chest. In said Chest, you may find the Schematic for the Tier 2 Rocket.
