You can make a closed off base on the Moon and with an Oxygen Sealer you can fill it up with Oxygen, meaning you won't need your oxygen gear in there anymore. You can also use an Oxygen Bubble Distributer to create a bubble that does the exact same without having a closed off area.
On Mars you can find Desh.
While exploring Mars or its moons, you may find a Tier 2 Dungeon.
The Electrolyzer allows you to separate Water into Oxygen and Hydrogen.
While exploring Venus or Mercury, you may find a Tier 4 Dungeon.
Mercury has an extremely high temperature as well as a decent amount of radiation, so you best be prepared.
Getting to Mercury is sure worth the trouble as it has 3 useful materials.
On Jupiter, your Tier 4 Thermal Padding and Tier 1 Space Suit won't be of much use.
On Ceres and Europa, you may encounter some weird types of Water.
Jupiter is massive, so of course it'll have something useful, right?
To survive on Saturn you are going to need a Tier 3 Space Suit, yet the only good thing you get on it is Magnesium.
While exploring Saturn or its moons, you may find a Tier 6 Dungeon.
The Infinity Catalyst is a combination of all the Singularities and utility items from Avaritia.

Infinity Ingots are what you need for crafting every creative item. They are hard to make, but luckly, once you make one, you can turn into Nuggets that you can then quadruple with the Atomic Multiplier.
With Infinity Ingots, you can make several tools with which you could destroy a dimension.
Infinity Armor is truly the best armor in the game, making you resistant to all types of damage.
You can use Clippers on plants in Crop Sticks to obtain Clippings of them, which you can plant on other Crop Sticks. That essentially allows you to duplicate crops.
The Insightful Condenser collects experience in a large area in front of it.
You are able to cross-breed the most basic of Seeds to make Carrots and Sugar Canes.
You can craft Horns that, when used, will destroy certain blocks nearby.
Instead of manually using Horns, you can make Horns that will be activated when hit with a Mana Burst.
The Ring of Aura passivly generates Mana when worn.
The Alchemy Catalyst, when placed below your Mana Pool, allows you to transmute many more items with it.
The Conjuration Catalyst, when placed below your Mana Pool, allows you to duplicate certain items with it.
Mana Blasters are in theory portable Mana Spreaders i.e. you can use them to manually shoot Mana Bursts.
You can infuse Incense Sticks with a potion effect with the Botanical Brewery and put it on an Incense Plate to apply that potion effect to all players in a 30 block radius.
Tainted Blood Pendants can be infused with a potion effect with the Botanical Brewery and when worn, as long as you have enough Mana, you will have that potion effect applied to you.
The Arcane Ensorcellator uses certain items and Essence of Knowledge to create enchantments.

The Heat Exchanger is a shapeless multiblock structure that uses Hot salt coolants to heat up Water into Steam or Superheated Steam, which can be used for power, making the coolants reusable in the process. That will only happen if the hot coolant and Water are travelling in Tubes next to each other in opposite directions.
Etherial (and Ineffable Glass) is Glass that players can go through, but no other mobs can.
The Energy Infuser charges items faster than anything else.
The Advanced Dislocator allows you to instantly teleport to a certain, already specified place.
With Mica you can make Speed, Piezo and Accuracy Modifiers with which you can replace the Null Modifiers of your ET multiblocks to upgrade them.
Heavy Water can be obtained by pumping out Water with an Electric Pump with a Filter Upgrade.
The Black Hole Unit and Tank can store large amounts of one type of items or fluid. You can put multiple of them in a Controller to be able to store even more items in one block.
You've completed every quest on Life In The Forest!
If you're playing on a server, you could send items to people in a Letter, even when they aren't online. If you aren't, I guess you could send yourself a Letter.

The Escritoire will allow you to enhance the breed chances of Bees, through a simple puzzle that you can make easier by adding Drones to it. Of course, this only works if you are breeding them the normal way.
With a Rainmaker, you can create or stop rain.

The ME Capability Adaptor allows you to connect your ME system with whatever is inside a Compact Machine, by having one inside of it, next to a Tunnel and one next to it, on the corresponding side of the block.
The Ember Spread Burst allows you to separately output Ember from all of its sides, while the Ember Funnel can concentrate Ember from multiple sources into one machine.
You can use a Hang Glider for, well, gliding around the void.
You can use an XP Drain for turning Experience on the ground or your own XP into a liquid, storable in Tanks.
The /dev/null/ will automatically collect an item you select. It will keep a stack of it and void the rest.
The Dark Matter Warper uses Dark Matter to trasmute mobs around it into other mobs. It also damages players when they are near it.
The Smart Combustion Controller allows you to fully automate combustion by selecting which items can be made in it. The items closer to the left will be made first and it can do 10 recipes/s.
Light Matter machines are the most efficient, but use Light Matter to work.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Cold Never Bothered Me Anyway
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Light Matter Freezer is the best Freezer in the game.
You can add a few blocks to your End Portal Core to get rid of those pests.
The Wildlife Attractor uses power, Water and Plant Matter to attract animals on top of it.
You can shift+right-click with a Health Gem to fill it up with Life Points.
You can put a Health Gem in a Life Injector in order to fill it up with the health from the mobs on top of it.
You can build a multiblock Life Infuser in order to automate the life infusion process.
Sprinklers sprinkle Water in a 9x9 area.
The Dark Matter Warper will turn Zombie Villagers into Illagers (Vindicators and Evokers).

You can add an Ancient Motive Core to tools that are on a Dawnstone Anvil for them to start gaining heat when used.

 After they've gained a good amount of heat, you can drop them into an Inferno Forge to add a modifier slot to them and then you'll be able to add certain modifiers to them with the Dawnstone Anvil.
Fans, when given a Redstone signal, push mobs.

While it may be a void, you can use the Nether for making Gold farms, but most importantly, for obtaining Blaze Rods from Blazes. You can build a large Netherrack platform for Blazes to spawn or you can locate a nether fortress and build to it.
The Survivalist's Fishing Rod is a fast unbreakable Fishing Rod that can fish out junk, Wood, Dirt and Saplings.
The 1K Fluid Storage Cell can store 1024mb of fluid.
The Compressed Rock Crusher is faster and more efficient than the regular one and can grind compressed blocks.

The Compressed Cactus gives you more Cactus Needles for less hearts, does a large amount of damage to mobs, can have Water extracted from it, can be cut (you can use a Compressed Knife on it) for getting 18 Cactus Fruit and can be grown on Compressed Sand.
Knives can be used for cutting Cacti into Cactus Fruit, Melons (the blocks) into 9 Melons (the items), Logs into 6 Planks and Planks into 6 Sticks.
The 256K Storage Cell can store 262144 items.
The 1024K Storage Cell can store 1048576 items.
The 4096K Storage Cell can store 4194304 items.
You can use Wires, similar to those from Immersive Engineering, instead of Cables for your network.

Instead of havng them as full blocks, you can turn ME Drives and Storage Cells into Fixtures that have a bit more than half the storage space, but can can share a block space with Cables, Terminals,...
You can make your ME Drives blast resistant, but they'll have less space.
This unlocks early-game Sky Resources and Sky Compression.
This unlocks Factory Tech and BuildCraft Transport.
This unlocks Botania and Boutanomy..
Complete this quest after updating the pack. It's advised that you back up before doing so.
While exploring Jupiter or its moons, you may find a Tier 5 Dungeon.
This unlocks Immersive Engineering, Petroleum and Tech and Alternating Flux.
The 1K Gas Storage Cell can store 1024mb of gas.
This unlocks Embers and Soot.
This unlocks Iron Chests, Colossal Chests, MultiStorage and EnderTanks.
This unlocks Astral Sorcery.
This unlocks Mekanism and Mekanism Generators.
The 4K Gas Storage Cell can store 4096mb of gas.
This unlocks Industrial Foregoing and Industrial Meat.
This unlocks Thermal Foundation, Expansion and Dynamics.
This unlocks Forestry.
This unlocks Actually Additions.
This unlocks the Seared stuff of Tinker's Construct, Tinker I/O and PlusTIC.
This unlocks NuclearCraft, Extreme Reactors and Advanced Generators.
This unlocks Environmental Tech, ET Lunar and Environmental Materials.
This unlocks GalactiCraft, Space Progression and Extra Planets.
This unlocks The Twilight Forest.
This unlocks Extra Utilities and Inventory Generators.
This unlocks EvilCraft and Blood Magic.
This unlocks Silent's Gems, the Spectre stuff from Random Things and Magical Psi.
The 4K Fluid Storage Cell can store 4096mb of fluid.
This unlocks end-game Sky Resources.
This unlocks Pam's HarvestCraft, Cooking For Blockheads and Rock Candy.
This unlocks Draconic Evolution.
This unlocks Calculator, Flux Networks and Integrated Dynamics and Tunnels.
This unlocks Tech Reborn.
This unlocks Mystical Agriculture and Agradditions.
This unlocks Applied Energistics 2, ExtraCells2, ME Capabilities, AE2 Stuff and Immersive Cables.
This unlocks Chickens, More Chickens and Roost.
This unlocks PneumaticCraft: Repressurized and Compact Machines.
This unlocks the Bee part of Forestry, Gendustry, Binnie's Mods and Magic Bees.
This unlocks Avaritia and creative items.
This unlocks RFTools, RFTools Dimensions and XNet.
The 16K Fluid Storage Cell can store 16384mb of fluid.
The 16K Gas Storage Cell can store 16384mb of gas.
The 64K Gas Storage Cell can store 65536mb of gas.
The 64K Fluid Storage Cell can store 65536mb of fluid.
The 256K Gas Storage Cell can store 262144mb of gas.
The 256K Fluid Storage Cell can store 262144mb of fluid.
The 1024K Gas Storage Cell can store 1048576mb of gas.
The 1024K Fluid Storage Cell can store 1048576mb of fluid.
The 4096K Gas Storage Cell can store 4194304mb of gas.
The 4096K Fluid Storage Cell can store 4194304mb of fluid.
The Rosa Arcana uses the experience on the ground near it or that of a player that's standing neat it to generate Mana.
The 16384K Storage Cell can store 16777216 items.
The Livingwood Avatar, when given Mana, automatically uses Rods.
You can make Soul Sand by freezing Sandy Netherrack.
The Vacuum Hopper automatically collects items and experience in an area.
The Core Charger allows you to charge Unprimed Energy Cores. If your Core reaches 100 percent, this machine will explode, therefore it's best to charge it to about 80 percent.
The Leadstone Jetpack uses RF to function. In only stores 80kRF, but uses 32RF/t.
The Hardened Jetpack holds 400kRF and uses 50RF/t.
The Reinforced Jetpack holds 4MRF and uses 200RF/t.
The Resonant Jetpack holds 20MRF and uses 450RF/t.
The Flux-Infused Jetplate holds 60MRF and uses 850RF/t, but also works as a Flux-Infused Chestplate.
Forestry offers a few Engines for generating RF.
In Kitchensink Mode you may play through any mod you want at any time. There will still be many quests to complete that will keep you playing for a while.

In Staged Mode to progress through one mod you need to progress through another. Even though there are no recipe changes, not being able to use certain items adds a layer of difficulty. However, if you dislike a certain mod, you can simply rush through its quests.
The Wither Builder automatically builds the Wither a block above it, allowing you to hide it under blast-proof blocks.
You Creative Modifier, when apllied to a tool, adds a modifier to it.
The Asgardandelion produces and endless amount of Mana.
The Creative Ember Source holds and infinite amount of ember.
The Creative Energy Cell holds and infinite amount of AE.
Creative Capacitors hold an infinite amount of RF, but of course, can only be used in your inventory.
The Creative RF Source, holds an infinite amount of RF, as a block.

For quickly going up and down, you can have a Pneumatic Elevator. To construct one, you are going to need Elevator Bases at the bottom, which can be stacked on top of each other to increase the maximum expansion hight of the elevator, Elevator Frames stacked on top of them, which determine how high the elevator can expand, and Elevator Callers, which represent the different floors. For the elevator to work, it's of course going to need a constant supply of pressure. If you find it being too slow, just add a few Speed Upgrades to it to make it almost instant.
You can put Elevator in the same vertical plane and jump between them.
The Jetpack from Mekanism uses Hydrogen to function.
The Sleeping Bag allows you to sleep anywhere.
Snad and Red Snad allow Cacti and Sugar Canes on top of them to grow 2 times faster, while Soul Snad allows Nether Warts on top of it to grow 4 times faster.
This unlocks ProjectE and Equivalent Energistics.
If you have an automatic mob farm, you probably have a huge influx of Loot Bags. You can make a Bag Opener to automatically open them.
Dark Glass is Glass that stops light from going through it.

The Vortex Tube uses pressure to make one side really hot and the other really cold. You can put Compressed Iron Blocks next to the hot side to transfer the heat to them and then the blocks adjacent to them. If you transfer this heat to a Furnace it'll use that heat instead of fuel. The higher the heat, the faster the Furnace will run.
The Electrostatic Compressor creates pressure when struck by lightning.
The Hyvecynth uses mana to generate bees.
The Beegonia uses Bees to generate mana.
The Hibeescus uses mana to turn Ignoble Bees Pristine.
The Sequencial Fabricator is a simple autocrafter, but when given the Fluid Fabrication Augment it will use fluids that are piped to it in recipes, allowing you to make TE alloys much faster.
Alchemical Chests and Bags work similarly to a personal EnderLink Chest.
Covalence Dusts are a basic crafting component in ProjectE.

To start with ProjectE, you are going to need a Philospher's Stone. It allows you to in-world transmute blocks, can be used as a portable Crafting Table and can transmute vanilla materials in a crafting grid.
With 4 Coal, you can make Alchemical Coal.
The Transmutation Table allows you to burn items into EMC and use that EMC for creating other items.
With 4 Alchemical Coal, you can make Mobius Fuel.
With 4 Mobius Fuel, you can make Aeternalis Fuel. It can burn through 612 items.
Alchemical Dark Matter can be used for upgrading your ProjectE machines.
Red Matter is an end-game material in ProjectE.
A Klein Star can be used for storing EMC. The first one can store 24576 EMC.
The second Klein Star is crafted with 4 of the fist one. The second one can store 98304 EMC.
The third Klein Star can store 393216 EMC.
The fourth Klein Star can store 1572864 EMC.
The fifth Klein Star can store 6291456 EMC.
The sixth Klein Star can store 25165824 EMC.
The Dark Matter Pedestal allows certain items from ProjectE to work with an area of effect.
Gem Armor, while it's not the most damage-resistant one, has many useful abilities.
The Energy Collector passively generates EMC. Mk1 can store 10k EMC and transfer 4EMC/t.
The Anti-Matter Relay Mk3 can output 640EMC/t and store 10M EMC.
The Energy Collector Mk2 can store 30k EMC and transfer 12EMC/t.
The Energy Collector Mk3 can store 60k EMC and transfer 40EMC/t.
Anti-Matter Relays collect EMC from adjacent Energy Collectors. Mk1 can output 64EMC/t and store 100k EMC.
The Anti-Matter Relay Mk2 can output 192EMC/t and store 1M EMC.
The Energy Condenser automatically burns items into EMC to create a certain item.
The Energy Condenser Mk2 is much faster than the first one and has an input and output side.

The Indexer allows you to interact with multiple inventories, as long as they are connected to it via Transfer Pipes. It doesn't require power to function, but getting items out of it takes a while and you need at least 8 GP for it to work.
Creative Essence is the final Essence.
Sugarcane and Pumpkin Seeds open up a huge range of new Seeds that you can make with cross-breeding. This includes: Scallion, Pumpkin, Cactus, Sweet Potato and Barley Seeds.
Crop Supports make adjacent crops grow faster.

P2P (Point to Point) Tunnels allow you to transfer channels from one place to another without having to use multiple Dense Cables. The Cable on which they are still however needs power, which you can transfer to it via a Quartz Fiber.

You can use the Quantum Singularities you made for transferring your ME system across large distances or dimensions. For that you need to place them in a multiblock consisting of a Quantum Link Chamber surrounded by 8 Quantum Rings in the form of a ring.

Gated Mode is just like Staged Mode, but to unlock the next stage you need to hand in certain items from the required stages. That means that you need to progress through every mod and you can't simply rush through them.
With a few machines and resources, you are able to make Anti-Rad.

It seems that the deeper you go into space, the duller everything becomes.
While exploring Uranus or its moons, you may find a Tier 7 Dungeon.
To survive on Neptune, you are going to need a Tier 4 Space Suit. There you can find Blue Gems and Space Zinc.
While exploring Neptune or its moons, you may find a Tier 8 Dungeon.
On Pluto you can find Space Tungsten.
While exploring Pluto, you may find a Tier 9 Dungeon.
On Eris you can find Dark Iron.

While exploring Eris, you may find a Tier 10 Dungeon. You probably know how it works by now. You kill the boss get the Key and then the Schematic. However, there are 2 Tier 10 Rockets, the regular one and the electric one. That's why, to complete this quest you need to get one or the other.
You've explored everything that you could in your solar system, but there might be something interesting on a planet in a nearby solar system.
With Melon Seeds, you now have everything needed to start cross-breeding Mystical Flowers.
Alchemical Glass gives more Crystal Shards than regular Glass.
Tier 3 has 3 Seeds from Pam's HarvestCraft.
It's midly interesting that there are 4 tier 3 Seeds and 3 tier 4 Seeds, isn't it?
Yet again, 5 tier 5 Seeds. Sadly, this will be last time something like that happens.
Celery is the only Tier 6 Seed. #4everAlone
There are also 2 tier 7 Seeds, but this will the last tier of Seeds that come in a pair.
Tier 8, half way there.
There are only 3 tier 9 Seeds. 3 squared gives 9, so this is still mildly, midly interesting, ain't it?
Now, 10/2 is 5. There are 5 tier 10 Seeds. I hope you're keeping up.
There are only 3 tier 11 Seeds. Without sounding crazy, I can't really make this sound interesting. Oh well.
And once again, 5 tier 2 Seeds. I guess I should remind you that you're 3/4 of the way there.
Maybe I should have told you the bad news first; there are 7 tier 13 Seeds. That's the most Seeds of a single tier there have been.
It's the same for tier 14, sadly. At least it's mildly interesting here as 14/2 is 7.
Tier 15, the second-to-last tier.
Who would have guessed that Candleberry Seeds are the end of your journey of cross-breeding Seeds. I hope you had fun.
You can throw Rudimentary Snares at hostile mobs and once they get white particles, you can kill them in order to obtain a Demonic Will.
The Hellfire Forge uses will to combine certain items into Reagents and tools.
You can make a Blood Altar and fill it up with your Life Points by using a Sacraficial Dagger.

Using the Hellfire Forge, you can make Arcane Ashes. When placed on the ground, they will allow you to make Sigils. One of those Sigils is the Divination Sigil that allow you to see information about the Blood Altar and your Blood network.

You can use your Blood Altar to create a Blood Orb. The Blood Orb is what allows you to interact with your Blood network. You can right-click it to transfer some of your helth to your Blood network or you can put it in a Blood Altar to add the LP in it to your network.
The Alchemy Table uses LP from your Blood network to create certain items.

The Incense Altar enhances your Sacrificial Dagger, when your near it, allowing you to use up almost all your health at once, but gives you a bonus over using your using the Sacrificial Dagger the regular way. The bonus increases by having certain natural blocks and Paths near it. After using the enhanced Sacrifial Dagger you get Soulfrey, so only use it if you have a good bonus.
You can use an Inspectoris Scandalum on your Blood Altar to see what you are going to need in order to upgrade it to the next tier. Tier 2 and 3 just require a few Blank Slates.
Instead of using a Sacrificial Dagger on yourself, you can attack mobs near the Blood Altar with a Dagger of Sacrifice to fill it up with their LP.

You can make rituals by having a Master Ritual Stone surrounded with Ritual Stones in a certain pattern and then inscribing them with the correct Elemental Insription Tools. You can make a Ritual Diviner that does all that for you.
With a tier 4 Blood Altar, you are able to make a Dusk Inscription Tool. With it you can make some more complex and useful rituals.

You can use a Demon Crucible to release the will from a Tartaric Gem into the chunk and then you can use a Demon Crystallizer to turn the will in the chunk into a Will Crystal. You'll have a chance of getting a higher tier one, that you can combine with a Tartaric Gem to upgrade it to that tier. Releasing the will from that Tartaric Gem will give you a higher chance of getting the Will Crystal for that tier and small chance for getting the one from the next tier and so on.
The Slice N' Splice uses an Axe and Shears for creating advanced EIO crafting components.
Vibrant Alloy is an alloy of Endergetic Alloy and Ender Pearls.
The regular Alloy Smelter can create EnderIO alloys and smelt 3 items at a time.
The Soul Binder uses items and mobs trapped in Soul Vials to create different items.

While other mods have Cables and Pipes, EnderIO's Conduits are probably the most useful ones to exist. You can put multiple of them in a block space and have multiple things going from and to different locations.
The Combustion Generator uses hot and cold fluids to generate RF.

Instead of using Rudimentary Snares to collect Demonic Wills, you can kill them with a Sentient Sword to fill up Tartaric Gems with will. Once you fill up a Tartaric Gem, you can make one that has a higher capacity.

By adding a Binding Reagent to an alchemy circle, it will allow you to turn Diamond tools into Bound ones. You can activate their special ability, but that will cause them to slowly drain LP from your network. When activated, the Bound Blade gives hostile mobs a chance of dropping a Blood Shard.

Although other mods allow you to teleport from a specific block to another or in a specific direction, EnderIO allows you to, using the Staff of Traveling, teleport to Teleport Anchors placed around your base. That way, as long as you're in range, you can teleport to specific blocks from anywhere.
The Soul Machine Chassis is needed for crafting all Soul EIO machines.
The Wireless Charger wirelessly charges items in your inventory in a small range.
The Attraction Obelisk can attract mobs towards it.
While there are other ways of preventing mob spawns, the Aversion Obelisk is probably the most configurable and has the biggest range.
The Weather Obelisk can change the weather by using certain fluids.
Killer Joe can use a weapon on mobs in an area in front of it. However, it requires Nutrient Destillation to work.

In order to unlock new pages in the Thaumonomicon, you are going to need research. To obtain research, you can either scan things with the Thaumometer or play a game in the Research Table.
Nitor is a light source and a heat sorce for the Crucible, which it is made in.
Using the Focal Manipulator, in the form of a puzzle, you are able to put a spell on a Focus and cast it using a Caster's Gauntlet.
The Worktable Charger gives your Arcane Worktable access to the aura in a 3x3 area of chunks.
You are able to create Golems for automating various things in ThaumCraft.
The Essentia Smeltery lets you smelt items into essentia, that can then be stored in Jars and Phials.

As you progress through ThaumCraft, you will gain warp, which gives you unwanted effects every so often. By purifying Water with Purifying Bath Salts and jumping in it, you'll temporarily get rid of all your warp.
Alchemical Fusion is a crafting mechanic in ThaumCraft that uses items from surrounding Pedestals and essentia from nearby Jars in order to create a certain item.
The Goggles of Revealing allow you to see the amount of essentia in ThaumCraft blocks.
The Crucible can simply be automated by putting 2 Alchemical Constructs on top of it.
You are able to use Mirrors how wirelessly transferring essentia and items.
